====================================================
 evdaemon-admin - Tools for evdaemon administration
====================================================

.. contents::

Description
===========

The Code Grove evdaemon-admin provides handy tools for configuring and
controlling `evdaemon <http://codegrove.org/evdaemon/>`_.

General information
===================

- **Author**: Tuomas Räsänen (tuos) <tuos@codegrove.org>
- **Homepage**: http://codegrove.org/evdaemon-admin/
- **License**: GPLv3+ (see COPYING for details)
- **Version**: 0.1

Runtime requirements
====================

- Evdaemon 0.3.x
- Python 2.6.x
- PyGTK

Downloading
===========

- Tarball is available at: http://codegrove.org/evdaemon-admin/releases/evdaemon-admin-0.1.tar.gz
- Tarballs of every release at: http://codegrove.org/evdaemon-admin/releases/
- Latest sources from public git-repository: http://github.com/tuos/evdaemon-admin/ ::

    git clone git://github.com/tuos/evdaemon-admin.git

Installing
==========

Ubuntu
------

The recommended way to install evdaemon-admin is to
`add it's PPA to your system <https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/codegrove>`_.
This allows you to treat evdaemon-admin as any other Ubuntu package.

Other systems
-------------

The install-procedure adheres the "standard"::

  python setup.py build && sudo python setup.py install

Bug reporting
=============

Report bugs by sending email to tuos@codegrove.org or by opening an issue
at http://github.com/tuos/evdaemon-admin/issues .
